# Extension Fabric: operator-placed extensions live under
# ~/.interceptor/extensions (covered by .interceptor/ above). Also ignore a
# repo-ROOT extension drop + the operator trust config, so capability-specific
# extension payloads are never accidentally committed to the capability-blind core.
# Root-anchored so docs/extensions/ (the authoring guide) stays tracked.
/extensions/
extension-trust.json
# Belt-and-suspenders: the operator reference extension `native-managed-copy`
# (re-signs / audits a local managed COPY of owned, third-party, or Apple apps)
# must NEVER be committed to this repo. It lives only under ~/.interceptor/extensions
# (outside this repo). Re-signing or modifying Apple / third-party software may have
# licensing implications — e.g. the Apple Developer Agreement / macOS SLA
# (https://developer.apple.com/support/terms/#apple-developer-agreement) — that are
# the operator's responsibility to assess. Keeping this capability out of the repo and
# the shipped product is deliberate. Ignore it by
# name anywhere, in case a copy is ever dropped in-repo.
native-managed-copy/
**/native-managed-copy/
reports/
use-cases/deep-research-demo/
# Apple container runtime data dir (symlinked from ~/Library/Application Support/com.apple.container/)
# Holds Linux container images + per-container VM disk state; never tracked.
.container-data/
